No static fields are skipped while using these [lombok][1] annotations

    @NoArgsConstructor
    @RequiredArgsConstructor
    @AllArgsConstructor

&gt;Static fields are skipped by these annotations.

If you want to declare constructor with static fields then you can declare the one explicitly, but you might end up with compiler error if any of those constructors have same signature

&gt;Unlike most other lombok annotations, the existence of an explicit constructor does not stop these annotations from generating their own constructor. This means you can write your own specialized constructor, and let lombok generate the boilerplate ones as well. **If a conflict arises (one of your constructors ends up with the same signature as one that lombok generates), a compiler error will occur.**

  [1]: https://projectlombok.org/features/constructor

